-- EU Carbon Allowances Stabilize After Slumping to Record Low
-- B y   E w a   K r u k o w s k a
-- 2013-01-14T07:51:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-14/eu-carbon-allowances-stabilize-after-slumping-to-record-low.html
European Union carbon allowances for
December regained ground after falling to a record low of 5.85
euros a metric ton in early trading today.  The contract was unchanged at 5.92 euros on the ICE Futures
Europe exchange as of 7:44 a.m. in  London . It has dropped 11.2
percent this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ewa Krukowska in Brussels at 
 ekrukowska@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lars Paulsson at   lpaulsson@bloomberg.net  